Here are both approaches side by side.

**1. Register the route in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

**2. Navigate from `ProductListPage` (two approaches):**

```csharp
// --- Approach A: query-string parameter (string ID only) ---
async void OnProductSelected_StringParam(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");
}

// --- Approach B: pass the full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters ---
async void OnProductSelected_FullObject(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
}
```

**3. Receive both in the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string ID from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, etc.
        }

        // Approach B — full object passed directly
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel to the page:**

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string (`?key=val`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Data type** | Strings only | Any object |
| **Serialization** | Values become strings | No serialization — passed by reference |
| **Deep-link friendly** | Yes (URI-safe) | No (in-process only) |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, filters | Complex/full objects |

Both approaches call the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` method, so you can support either or both in one ViewModel. Always `await` the `GoToAsync` call to avoid race conditions.
